# Filtering
- Update to filter based on expected modifcations - propionyl at N-term and K, etc.

## CHiMA filter

### MSFragger
This filters peptides based on the number of match fragments. It keeps those that have at least 50% matched fragments out of the theoretical total
- This might be improved as it may not be reasonable to only consider the theoretical total and more like the empirical
- Remove duplicate PSMs and keep the one that has more fragment matches
```{r}
searchRes.chimaFilter <-  searchRes %>%
  mutate(prop_ions_matched = num_matched_ions / tot_num_ions) %>%
  filter(prop_ions_matched >= 0.5) %>%
  group_by(ModifiedPeptideSequenceCharge) %>%
  arrange(desc(prop_ions_matched), .by_group = TRUE) %>%
  slice(1) %>%
  ungroup()

# summary
n_before <- nrow(searchRes)
n_after <- nrow(searchRes.chimaFilter)
percent_filtered <- (n_before - n_after) / n_before * 100

cat("Peptides before filtering:", n_before, "\n")
cat("Peptides after filtering:", n_after, "\n")
cat("Percent filtered out:", round(percent_filtered, 2), "%\n")
```

### Spectral library
```{r}
specLib.chimaFilter <- specLib %>%
  filter(ModifiedPeptideSequenceCharge %in% searchRes.chimaFilter$ModifiedPeptideSequenceCharge)

# summary
n_before <- length(unique(specLib$ModifiedPeptideSequenceCharge))
n_after <- length(unique(specLib.chimaFilter$ModifiedPeptideSequenceCharge))
percent_filtered <- (n_before - n_after) / n_before * 100

cat("Peptides before filtering:", n_before, "\n")
cat("Peptides after filtering:", n_after, "\n")
cat("Percent filtered out:", round(percent_filtered, 2), "%\n")

# output
write.table(specLib.chimaFilter, "specLib_filtered.tsv",
            sep = "\t",
            quote = FALSE,
            row.names = FALSE)
```

